&lt;div class="outline-text-2" id="text-org9dc2f0b"&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id="outline-container-org264268d" class="outline-3"&gt;
&lt;h3 id="org264268d"&gt;Proximate Layout&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org264268d"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
How well are related items placed near each other? Do the edges cross or do items overlap when perhaps they do not need to?
Are the crossings distracting?
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id="outline-container-org304fbc4" class="outline-3"&gt;
&lt;h3 id="org304fbc4"&gt;Design of the Visulization&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org304fbc4"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Dose the visualization effectively use the assignment of variables to elements and design of a visualization?
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id="outline-container-orgc012829" class="outline-3"&gt;
&lt;h3 id="orgc012829"&gt;Contest&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="outline-text-3" id="text-orgc012829"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
How interesting is the result? Does this represent an interesting choice of data and/or an interesting way to display the data?
&lt;/p&gt;
